Global Partially Oriented Yarn (POY) Market Insights
Partially Oriented Yarn (POY) Market size was valued at USD 10.85 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 15.21 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.9% from 2024 to 2030.

Partially Oriented Yarn (POY) Market Overview
The global market for Partially Oriented Yarn (POY) has witnessed significant growth, valued at USD 10.1 billion in 2023 and expected to reach USD 14.2 billion by 2028, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5%. POY is an essential raw material used in the production of polyester filament yarns, widely employed in the textile and apparel industry. POY's unique properties, such as its semi-oriented structure, make it suitable for processes like texturizing and drawing, contributing to its high demand in various industries, including fashion, automotive, and home textiles. This growing demand from these end-use industries drives market growth and expansion globally.

